{# ---- 17. Prose ------------------------------------------------------------ #}
<div class="showcase__item">
  <div class="container showcase__meta">
    <p class="showcase__label">17. prose (drop-cap longform)</p>
    <p class="showcase__note">call s.prose({ dropCap, width, tone }) with a body block. Generous measure and leading, serif subheads, and a navy serif drop-cap on the opening paragraph. For approach pages and posts.</p>
  </div>
  {% call s.prose({ dropCap: true }) %}
    <p>Most people who come in for anxiety have already tried very hard to think their way out of it. They have read the books, rehearsed the conversations, and planned for outcomes that never arrived. The trying is real, and so is the exhaustion that comes with it. What tends to help is not more effort, but a different relationship with the alarm itself.</p>
    <p>So we get curious instead of forceful. What is the worry protecting? When does it fire, and what does it cost you to keep obeying it? Those questions sound simple, and they are not, but they are where the work usually begins.</p>
    <h3>How the work actually goes</h3>
    <p>It is solution-focused and practical, and it moves at your pace. We pay attention to the thoughts and to the body, because anxiety lives in both, and we start by making sure you feel genuinely understood. Not managed, not processed, understood.</p>
  {% endcall %}
</div>

